If you have Boost >= 1.36.0 installed:
   ./bjam
   ./bjam install --prefix=/usr #optional

If you only want the query code and do not care about compression (.gz, .bz2, and .xz):
  ./compile_query_only.sh

Windows:
  The windows directory has visual studio files.
  Note that you need to compile the kenlm project before build_binary and ngram_query projects
  but this happens automatically if you build the whole solution.
  
  Visual Studio 2013 is used.
  
  Boost v1.55.0 should be installed in "C:\Program Files\boost\boost_1_55_0".
  You can download boost source from http://sourceforge.net/projects/boost/files/boost/1.55.0/
  You can download boost binaries from http://sourceforge.net/projects/boost/files/boost-binaries/1.55.0-build2/
  
  C:\Program Files\boost\boost_1_55_0
  - boost
  - lib32-msvc-12.0 (for Win32)
  - lib64-msvc-12.0 (for x64)
  - ...
